The nuchal plate is hexagonal in outline, wider than long (Pal. 1301: 
Fig. 2
E-H). It contacts the first pair of peripherals, the first pair of costals and the neural 1. The anterior border possesses a shallow nuchal notch, affecting the nuchal border and the first peripherals (Pal. 1300: 
Fig. 2A, B
). The anteroposterolateral sides of the nuchal are rather equal in length, whereas the posterior border is narrow and slightly convex anteriorly (
Fig. 2E, F
). In lateral view, the nuchal is vaguely curved (
Fig. 2I, J
). Two transversal thickenings are

